eriods of change.Roy's findings illustrate important theoretical issues in psychology and sociology, and her conclusions will greatly interest students of ethnic/race relations, conflict resolution, the sociology of violence, agrarian society, and South Asia.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCommunalismzBangladesh. 0aHinduszBangladesh. 0aMuslimszBangladesh. 7aRELIGION / Hinduism / General.2bisacsh  a1950s.  aagrarian society.  aanalysis.  aasian history.  abangladesh.  acommunity.  aconflict resolution.  aconflict.  adistribution of power.  aethnicity.  afirst person.  ahindu.  ainterview.  amemory.  amuslim.  aneighbors.  apower structure.  apsychology.  arace relations.  areligion.  areligious studies.  arevolution.  ariot.  asmall town.  asocial change.  asociology.  asouth asia.  atrue story.  aviolence.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z978311063534840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052091412440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520914124423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520914124/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY